Top Stories (January 5)

CALIFORNIA GOVERNOR, FEDERAL GOVERNMENT TOUGHEN STANCES ON POWER COSTS
Positions hardened Tuesday in a standoff between Gov. Gray Davis and the 
nation's top regulator of electricity over how to fix California's power 
crisis.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/01/05/krtbn/0000-0117-ES-POWER-COST

CALIFORNIA LAWMAKER INTRODUCES BILL TO EXTEND ELECTRIC RATE FREEZE
A California state assemblyman has introduced legislation that calls for a 
two-year extension of the retail electricity rate freeze for customers of 
Pacific Gas & Electric and Southern California Edison, and would allow the 
utilities to continue to collect an existing 10% surcharge from ratepayers to 
finance wholesale power costs.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/05/eng-djn/eng-djn_230029_47_7276272792369

CALIFORNIA ELECTRICITY CRISIS SENDS JOLT TO BANK LENDERS
The California electricity crisis is beginning to extend far beyond the 
state's borders.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
01/05/eng-djn/eng-djn_184038_125_061786614824

ALLEGHENY ENERGY SUBSIDIARY TO CONSTRUCT $400-MILLION POWER PLANT IN INDIANA 
- 630-MW MERCHANT FACILITY TO BE BUILT IN STAGES BEGINNING IN 2002
Allegheny Energy, Inc., announced today that its unregulated generation 
subsidiary, Allegheny Energy Supply Company, LLC, plans to construct a 
630-megawatt (MW) natural gas-fired merchant generating facility in St. 
Joseph County, Ind., approximately 10 miles west of South Bend.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/comtex/2
001/01/05/bw/0000-1898-md-allegheny-energy

NORTH CAROLINA COMMISSION TO ABANDON PLAN TO DEREGULATE STATE'S POWER MARKET
Prospects of a deregulated power market coming to North Carolina anytime soon 
were dimmed Thursday by a state panel concerned about California's 
deregulation horrors.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/01/05/krtbn/0000-0339-RA-ELECTRICITY

